President Obama has announced his intent to appoint three individuals to key Administration posts. General Larry R. Ellis, USA (Ret.) will be appointed as a member of the American Battle Monuments Commission. He has a long history of military service and currently serves as President and CEO of VetConnexx, LLC. Dr. Howard Z. Borin, a Board Certified Pediatrician, will be appointed as a member of the Commission on Presidential Scholars. He has extensive experience in pediatric medicine and has been recognized as one of the Best Doctors in America. Grace Tsao-Wu, currently a partner at Laudi Vidni, will also be appointed as a member of the Commission on Presidential Scholars. She has a background in business and has been involved in various organizations focused on education and community empowerment.